load ../infoflow-signal-carriage.maude

--- ============================ COVERAGE (violation reachable) =================

--- Coverage: trust is NOT fabricated. An internal signal emitted by an UNTRUSTED
--- rule (its payload joined an untrusted input) carries `untrusted` to the receiver,
--- which drives a trusted control sink -> injection. Carriage propagates the real
--- low label; it does not launder up just because the channel is internal.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-SIGNAL-CARRIAGE :
  internalSig(sigA) emit(sigA, untrusted) receiver(sigA) controlSink(trusted)
  =>* C:Cfg injection .

--- Coverage: NO LAUNDERING. An external `whip signal` injection of an INTERNAL
--- signal is refused -- the attacker cannot smuggle untrusted data in under a
--- trusted internal signal name.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-SIGNAL-CARRIAGE :
  internalSig(sigA) extInject(sigA)
  =>* C:Cfg laundering .

--- Coverage: an EXTERNAL-entry signal driving a trusted sink injects (stage a is
--- preserved -- an external entry point is the untrusted default, hand-classified).
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-SIGNAL-CARRIAGE :
  externalSig(sigB) receiver(sigB) controlSink(trusted)
  =>* C:Cfg injection .

--- Coverage: D2b invoke-selector NMIF. A selector rooted in the low-integrity
--- inbound payload for `invoke:<childB>` cannot gate a higher-integrity branch.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-SIGNAL-CARRIAGE :
  invokePayload(childB, untrusted) selectorRequires(childB, trusted)
  =>* C:Cfg invokeSelectorReject .

--- ============================ BITE (no violation) ===========================

--- Bite: THE stage-(b) WIN. An internal signal emitted by a TRUSTED rule carries
--- `trusted` to the receiver, which drives a trusted sink -- NO injection. The
--- internal flow propagated its emitter's trust automatically; no hand-vouching of
--- the signal name was needed. No solution.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-SIGNAL-CARRIAGE :
  internalSig(sigA) emit(sigA, trusted) receiver(sigA) controlSink(trusted)
  =>* injection RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: no external injection of an internal signal means no laundering. An
--- internal signal with only an in-system emitter never reaches the laundering
--- state. No solution.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-SIGNAL-CARRIAGE :
  internalSig(sigA) emit(sigA, trusted) receiver(sigA)
  =>* laundering RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: a trusted invoke payload may select a trusted branch. No solution.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-SIGNAL-CARRIAGE :
  invokePayload(childB, trusted) selectorRequires(childB, trusted)
  =>* invokeSelectorReject RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: a low invoke payload may select a low branch. No solution.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-SIGNAL-CARRIAGE :
  invokePayload(childB, untrusted) selectorRequires(childB, untrusted)
  =>* invokeSelectorReject RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: the selector check is target-specific; childB's payload does not authorize
--- or reject childC's branch. No solution.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-SIGNAL-CARRIAGE :
  invokePayload(childB, untrusted) selectorRequires(childC, trusted)
  =>* invokeSelectorReject RESIDUAL:Cfg .
